The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                  
	Melbourne: Retired Australia pacer Glenn McGrath said he cannot wait to see David Warner join him at the Delhi Daredevils nets for the Indian Premier League (IPL) this year, adding that he was quite in awe of the exciting youngsters big-hitting prowess.    
	The Daredevils recently signed the 22-year-old Warner well before the youngster made his memorable debut for the Australian team in a Twenty20 match against South Africa.        
	Calcutta: The members of the national selection committee will meet at the Cricket Centre at Wankhede stadium at noon Sunday to pick the squad for the upcoming tour of Sri Lanka, according to a BCCI release Friday.        
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has increased the pays and perks of the players in the new central contracts, this despite claims that it is facing a financial crisis.        
	New Delhi: Grandmaster Petr Kostenko of Kazakhstan defeated India hopeful Parimarjan Negi to stay in sole lead with seven points after the seventh round of the 7th Parsvnath International chess tournament Friday. A group of 10 players, including six-time national champion Surya Sekhar Ganguly, Abhijit Kunte and Dibyendu Barua trail the leader by a full point. Ganguly defeated Deep Sengupta, Kunte got the better of young IM Shyam Sundar while Barua beat Matta Vinay Kumar.        
	Abu Dhabi: Jeev Milkha Singhs sensational five-under 67 saw him zoom 51 places to tied 40th along with Jyoti Randhawa before darkness forced suspension of play in the second round of the Abu Dhabi Golf Championships, here Friday. S.S.P. Chowrasia, meanwhile, came tantalisingly close to making the cut. Suspension of play due to darkness left Shiv Kapur stranded at the 14th hole at two-under for the day. Australian Richard Green and Englishman Graeme Storm shared the lead.          
	Seoul: Indias mixed doubles pair of Jwala Gutta and V. Diju reached the semi-finals of the Yonex Korea Super Series defeating the Indonesian eighth-seed pair of Wijaya Rendra and Meiliana Jauhari, here Friday. The unseeded duo won 21-17, 16-21, 21-9.        
	Buenos Aires: Diego Maradona labelled the rules for Fifas World Player of the Year vote as stupid on Friday after rules prevented him from choosing Lionel Messi.        
	Madrid: Ramon Calderon resigned as president of Spanish champions Real Madrid on Friday.
                                                                                                                                                                     
